.TH "gether_disconnect" 9 "gether_disconnect" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gether_disconnect \- notify network layer that USB link is inactive
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" gether_disconnect
.BI "(struct gether *link "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "link" 12
the USB link, on which \fBgether_connect\fP was called
.SH "CONTEXT"
irqs blocked
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is called to deactivate endpoints and let the network layer know
the connection went inactive ("no carrier").

On return, the state is as if \fBgether_connect\fP had never been called.
The endpoints are inactive, and accordingly without active USB I/O.
Pointers to endpoint descriptors and endpoint private data are nulled.
